Functions

Const getNumber

  • getNumber(text: string): number | undefined

  • Extracts the first number from the string.

    If no numbers were found, returns empty array.

    getNumber('99.9 USD') // 99.9

    Parameters

    • text: string

    Returns number | undefined

Const getNumberRange

  • getNumberRange(value: string | number): object | object

  • Extracts number range from the string.

    getNumberRange('100-200') // { min: 100, max: 200 }

    Parameters

    • value: string | number

    Returns object | object

Const getNumbers

  • getNumbers(text: string): number[]

  • Extracts numbers from the string.

    If no numbers were found, returns empty array.

    getNumbers('10 20') // [10, 20]

    Parameters

    • text: string

    Returns number[]

Const makeUrl

  • makeUrl(url: string, prefix: string): string

  • Prepends the prefix to the url.

    Expects URL to start with '/', otherwise returns original URL with no prefix added.

    makeUrl('//foo.bar','https:') // 'https://foo.bar'
makeUrl('/baz','http://foo.bar') // 'https://foo.bar/baz'

    Parameters

    • url: string
    • prefix: string

    Returns string

Const parseHTML

  • parseHTML(spec?: Spec, postHandlers?: PostHandlers): Function

  • Creates parser function from parse descriptor and handler functions.

    Used with HTML data.

    const parse = parseHTML({
// HTML parse descriptor
})
const data = parse(htmlPage)

    Parameters

    • Default value spec: Spec = ""
    • Default value postHandlers: PostHandlers = {}

    Returns Function
